commText: Fraser-McGurk and Abishek Porel are at the crease. Fraser-McGurk is on strike. Wood will open the attack

Wood to Fraser-McGurk, FOUR, that's a good way to start! Pitched up full and straight on, easy pickings for Fraser-McGurk as it was on the pads, he whipped it away through the gap between mid-on and mid-wicket

Wood to Fraser-McGurk, FOUR, slammed down the ground! Full and just outside off this time, Fraser-McGurk stood still, cleared his front-leg a little and sliced it back over the bowler's head, not a clean strike but enough to go for four

Wood to Fraser-McGurk, SIX, this one is clean alright! Full and shaping into the pads, pulled the length back just a touch but it doesn't make a difference, Fraser-McGurk stands still and flicks it up and over the wide long-on ropes
Wood to Fraser-McGurk, no run, length delivery on off-stump, Fraser-McGurk bunts it towards mid-wicket, better length this time around and it hit the deck hard

Wood to Fraser-McGurk, FOUR, struck with disdain! Just back of a length and outside off, too much width on offer this time, Fraser-McGurk clears his front-leg again to open up the off-side and he slaps it very hard over cover, went flat and bounced just once before the ropes
Wood to Fraser-McGurk, 1 run, good length delivery on middle, tucked away to deep square leg, he retains the strike with that run, 19 runs off that first over!
Warner - Marsh Warner - Prithvi Prithvi - Fraser McGurk Fraser McGurk - Porel
Fourth opening pair for Delhi Capitals in IPL 2024 - joint most with Punjab Kings
Jasprit Bumrah, right-arm fast, comes into the attack

Bumrah to Fraser-McGurk, no ball, SIX, Bumrah greeted with a six! How often do you see that?! And to make matters even worse, it's a no-ball! Went for a slower delivery first up, was full and on off-stump, Fraser-McGurk picked it and hoisted it over long-on for a maximum

Bumrah to Fraser-McGurk, FOUR, and he capitalises on the free-hit as well! Bumrah went for the yorker on the stumps, Fraser-McGurk stood fairly deep in the crease, cleared his front-leg and drilled it back past his partner at the other end
Most runs in the first over of an innings for Delhi Capitals (IPL) 25 vs KKR Ahmedabad 2021 (Prithvi 24*) 19 vs MI Delhi 2008 (Sehwag 18*) 19 vs MI Delhi 2024 (Fraser McGurk 19*)
Bumrah to Fraser-McGurk, 1 run, full on middle, bunted into the leg-side towards mid-wicket for a quick single
Bumrah to Abishek Porel, no run, full on off-stump from round the wicket to the left hander, Abishek Porel prods forward to defend
Bumrah to Abishek Porel, no run, good length delivery on off-stump, Abishek Porel hangs back and tucks it straight to mid-wicket
Bumrah to Abishek Porel, wide, slower delivery and going down leg with the angle, another extra
Bumrah to Abishek Porel, 1 run, good length delivery on off-stump, knocked towards mid-on for a quick single

Bumrah to Fraser-McGurk, FOUR, the over ends with a boundary too! Length delivery on middle, again Fraser-McGurk stands till and swipes it away through mid-wicket, came off the inner half of the bat but had enough to reach the ropes
Nuwan Thushara, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
N Thushara to Abishek Porel, FOUR, Porel joins in on the fun! Full and straight on off-stump, right in the slot and Abishek Porel lofted it over mid-off with a free-flowing drive, that looked classy
Highest scores after first two overs in an IPL innings (non truncated matches) 40 RR vs KKR Kolkata 2023 40 SRH vs DC Delhi 2024 38 KTK vs RR Indore 2011 37 DC vs MI Delhi 2024 *
N Thushara to Abishek Porel, 1 run, full and straight on off-stump, checked his shot as he shoveled it out towards long-on who had just been pushed back, goes to him on the bounce

N Thushara to Fraser-McGurk, FOUR, he only plays one way! Pitched up full on off-stump, Fraser-McGurk backed away to make a bit of room before slicing it up and over extra cover, just bounced inside the ropes
Two men out on the ropes are deep square leg and deep mid-wicket
N Thushara to Fraser-McGurk, wide, pressure, he hurls one down leg, bit of bat or pad on this and it would've raced down past the keeper

N Thushara to Fraser-McGurk, FOUR, 50 up in no time! Tushara went for a yorker, overcooked it just a touch and it was on the pads, all Fraser-McGurk has to do was flick it away behind square on the leg-side and it was always going to be four
N Thushara to Fraser-McGurk, FOUR, smashed straight back at him! Stand and deliver again, length delivery on off-stump, Fraser-McGurk stood still and smacked it straight back past the bowler
N Thushara to Fraser-McGurk, no run, foxes him with a slower bouncer, Fraser-McGurk probably wasn't expecting the change of pace and went through with the pull too early, still a big over
19, 18 and 18 - that's how many the first three overs have gone for today
Piyush Chawla, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Chawla to Abishek Porel, 1 run, full on middle, gently pushed down towards long-on
Now, what will Fraser-McGurk's approach be against the spinner?

Chawla to Fraser-McGurk, SIX, absolutely the same is the answer! And he gets to 50 in 15 balls again! Floated up full on off-stump, right in the slot, Fraser-McGurk leant in and smoked it over deep mid-wicket with a clean strike

Fastest 50s for Delhi Capitals by balls faced 15 Fraser McGurk vs SRH Delhi 2024 15 Fraser McGurk vs MI Delhi 2024 * 17 C Morris vs GL Delhi 2016 18 R Pant vs MI Wankhede 2019 18 P Shaw vs KKR Ahmedabad 2021
Reaching 50 in 15 or fewer balls twice in T20 cricket Andre Russell Sunil Narine Jake Fraser McGurk

Chawla to Fraser-McGurk, FOUR, just past the man! Length delivery just outside off, was the wrong-un, Fraser-McGurk backed away and slapped it towards cover, man there ran to his left and leapt but it was just out of his reach
Chawla to Fraser-McGurk, 1 run, flatter delivery on off-stump, punched down to long-on
Chawla to Abishek Porel, 1 run, length delivery on the pads, whipped away to deep mid-wicket
Chawla to Fraser-McGurk, 1 run, fuller length on middle, Fraser-McGurk presses back and knocks it down the ground to long-on, he retains the strike with that run
Hardik Pandya, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Hardik Pandya to Fraser-McGurk, FOUR, no bowler is going to be spared it seems! Not a great delivery this, slower and back of a length outside off, lot of width and Fraser-McGurk slapped it up and over extra cover, one-bounce four
Hardik Pandya to Fraser-McGurk, no run, banged in short outside off again, Fraser-McGurk reached out and swatted it down towards mid-wicket

Hardik Pandya to Fraser-McGurk, SIX, another one goes into orbit! Full and straight on middle, right in the slot and you bet it disappeared, free swing of the bat and someone was catching it in the crowd at deep mid-wicket
Hardik Pandya to Fraser-McGurk, no run, banged in short on middle, zips through this time and beats his pull, called the second bouncer for the over

Hardik Pandya to Fraser-McGurk, FOUR, that's an extraordinary shot! Length delivery on middle-leg, Fraser-McGurk backed away a long way and just punched it on the up and over extra cover, trusted the pitch there and it came off

Hardik Pandya to Fraser-McGurk, SIX, Mumbai fans look away! Full and on the pads, he simply loves it there, he picked it up and swiped it away a long way over the deep square leg ropes, 20 off that over!

Over Summary (1-5 overs) -- Fraser-McGurk smashes 19 off the first over -- Even Bumrah isn't spared, 18 runs off his over -- Delhi bring up their 50 in 2.4 overs -- Fraser-McGurk hammers a 15-ball fifty -- Hardik comes on and is met with disdain, 20-run over
Jasprit Bumrah [1.0-0-18-0] is back into the attack
Bumrah to Abishek Porel, no run, back of a length on off-stump from round the wicket, hits the bat hard as Porel hangs back to defend
Bumrah to Abishek Porel, no run, back of a length on middle, tucked straight to square leg
Bumrah to Abishek Porel, 2 runs, good length delivery on middle, Abishek Porel shuffled across just a touch and just beat square leg to his left, couple taken as he fumbled as well
Bumrah to Abishek Porel, no run, length delivery on off-stump, bunted straight to square leg again
Bumrah to Abishek Porel, no run, wonderful over so far, slower delivery on middle, just short of length too, Abishek Porel was looking to run it down to third man and missed
Bumrah to Abishek Porel, 1 run, great over from Bumrah! Length delivery on off-stump, Abishek Porel hangs back and eases it towards backward point for a quick single

Timeout. You can understand why Mumbai needed a breather here. Continuing on the trend of high-scores this year, it looks like we have another one on the cards. JFM is hitting them with such ease, it's incredible to see.

Hardik Pandya to Abishek Porel, no run, Porel finds the fielder again, length delivery on off-stump and it's bunted straight to mid-wicket
Hardik Pandya to Abishek Porel, no run, another dot, length delivery on off-stump, bunted straight back to the bowler
Fraser-McGurk has been off-strike for a long time now, wonder what it would've done to his concentration and flow

Hardik Pandya to Abishek Porel, FOUR, poor delivery and put away! A drag-down that ends up well down leg, was asking to be put away and Abishek Porel helped it fine with a pull, got a little tickle and it raced away

Hardik Pandya to Abishek Porel, SIX, that's the 100-run stand up! Banged in short on middle, Abishek Porel was seemingly waiting for it, he hung back and hooked it away right over the deep backward square leg ropes

Hardik Pandya to Abishek Porel, 5 runs, tight-run and overthrows! Length delivery on off-stump, Abishek Porel bunted it towards mid-off and Fraser-McGurk was late to take off for the run, the throw back to the striker's end was good but Ishan Kishan was in no position to gather it and it went down to the ropes

Hardik Pandya to Fraser-McGurk, SIX, sliced in the air and well over the ropes! Very full and just outside off, Fraser-McGurk cleared his front-leg again and sliced it, hit it really well though and cleared long-off with ease
Piyush Chawla [1.0-0-14-0] is back into the attack
Chawla to Abishek Porel, 1 run, flatter length delivery outside off, Porel comes down the track and knocks it down to long-off
Chawla to Fraser-McGurk, no run, very full on leg-stump, Fraser-McGurk makes room again and knocks it towards cover
Chawla to Fraser-McGurk, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Chawla to Fraser-McGurk, out Caught by Nabi!! And the carnage has finally been brought to an end! Sensational innings from the young man but he has to go. A length delivery on middle-leg, was the wrong-un and turned back into him to further cramp him for room, he pressed back looking to heave it away over deep mid-wicket but it hit the inner part of the bat and the man stationed there took it easily. There was a record hundred there for the taking but a fine knock nonetheless. Mumbai finally get the breakthrough. Fraser-McGurk c Nabi b Chawla 84(27) [4s-11 6s-6]

Chawla to Shai Hope, 1 run, length delivery on middle-leg, worked away towards mid-wicket for one
Chawla to Abishek Porel, 1 run, length delivery outside off, dragged away to deep with a pull

Wood to Abishek Porel, 2 runs, length delivery just outside off, heaved away over mid-wicket and into the gap, not struck well enough to make it to the fence though, it's cut off

Wood to Abishek Porel, FOUR, that's very clever! Short of a length just outside off, Abishek Porel hung back and waited for it before cutting it up and over short third man, he didn't look to keep that down
Wood to Abishek Porel, no run, he's out for the count! Banged in short on middle-leg, kept coming into him and cramped him for room on the pull, looks like it struck him flush on the left wrist
Patrick Farhart the physio is out there, bit of magic spray and wrapping should do the trick. The umpire is trying to usher them off and get the game moving
Wood to Abishek Porel, 1 run, yorker on off-stump, Abishek Porel carves it out towards deep point for one
Wood to Shai Hope, 1 run, length delivery on off-stump, bunted towards mid-off for a quick single
Wood to Abishek Porel, no run, back of a length on off-stump, Abishek Porel hangs back and chops it straight to backward point

Nabi to Shai Hope, 1 run, length delivery on middle, Shai Hope presses back and works it away to deep mid-wicket

Nabi to Shai Hope, 1 run, length delivery on middle, worked away to deep mid-wicket
Nabi to Abishek Porel, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Nabi to Abishek Porel, out Caught by Ishan Kishan!! Nabi gets MI their second wicket! Flatter delivery outside off, Abishek Porel had made up his mind about running down the track and he got nowhere near the pitch of it, he swiped at it across the line and got a bottom edge that was pouched safely. Would've been out stumped if not caught behind. So MI doing really well to regain some control here after that early blitz. Abishek Porel c Ishan Kishan b Nabi 36(27) [4s-3 6s-1]
Rishabh Pant, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Nabi to Pant, 1 run, length delivery on off-stump, worked away towards deep mid-wicket, they thought of two as there was a fumble but decided against it

Nabi to Shai Hope, 1 run, very full on middle, pushed down the ground to long on

Nabi to Shai Hope, SIX, full-toss and he pays the price! Might've gone for the yorker but he pushed it a touch too full, ended up being a low full-toss and Shai Hope did well to get under it before lofting it straight back over the bowler's head for a biggie
Nabi to Shai Hope, 1 run, full on middle, mistimed slog sweep goes down to deep mid-wicket

Nabi to Shai Hope, SIX, DC back on track with a big over! Dragged down short on middle, rank half-tracker and Shai Hope heaved it away over the deep mid-wicket fence

17:20 Local Time, 11:50 GMT, 17:20 IST: DC end on 257 and it will be a steep chase for MI. Fraser-McGurk was absolutely sensational at the top as boundaries flew from his bat. Porel at the other end was happy to just watch it as he was striking at less than 100 at one point. Chawla finally got the South Australian and MI pegged things back a little. Hope though again upped the rate with a flurry of sixes before he went. And at the end it was Tristan Stubbs who went ballistic. Solid innings all around from DC and they have given themselves a good chance in this game. As far as the bowling of MI is concerned, Bumrah was the pick despite going for 18 in his first over. Chawla too bowled really well. The rest were hammered. Can MI chase it down? Back for the reply in 5 minutes...

Jake Fraser-McGurk: That’s my role, go out there and score as many as I can and get the team off to a nice start. Not at all, if I get ones and twos it’s probably off the last ball of the over or if I mis-hit it. It’s something I’ve always had, getting that base right and having the right stance.
